SAMUEL MARTIN , Knt., one of the Barons of Her Majesty's Court of Exchequer; Sir
JAMES DUKE , Bart., M.P.; Sir
FRANCIS GRAHAM MOON , Bart., F. S. A.; and Sir
ROBERT WALTER CARDEN , Knt.; Aldermen of the said City;
RUSSELL GURNET , Esq., Q. C., Recorder of the said City; WILLIAM FERNELEY ALLEN, Esq.;
JAMES ABBISS , Esq.; JOHN SILLS GIBBONS, Esq.; and
ANDREW LUSK , Esq., Aldermen of the said City;
THOMAS CHAMBERS , Esq., Q. C., Common Serjeant of the said City; and
ROBERT MALCOLM KERR , Esq., Judge of the Sheriffs Court; Her Majesty's Justices of Oyer and Terminer and General Gaol Delivery of Newgate, holden for the said City, and Judges of the Central Criminal Court.
